<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-08-31T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-08-31T04:00:00-05:00" n="84" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d84">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">124.60D/78: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Finland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Helsinki</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-31T12:00:00+03:00">August 31,
                                    1942—noon.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received August 31—8:17 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>734. Former Estonian Minister Varma told me last night in confidence that
                            this Legation and especially our Military Attaché are now kept under
                            regular surveillance by Finnish authorities including stationing of
                            official photographer in nearby houses to record all visitors.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Schoenfeld</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>